children.subject:
162 is dependant on a good group -- Most of my friends I went into the class WITH a group of friends they know, worked with before and can trust. I've heard stories of a hard carry a 162 project with 1 person only. 

16B is dependant on how much you liked 16A and your confidence in linear algebra. Medium-long homeworks and average to a little hard exams.

Data100 is a light-medium workload a lot of people like it though it might be full now (not sure) but lots of people recommend the class.

history.content: I’ve done three techs a semester for the past few semesters, but I kind of want to chill during Fall 2020. I’m taking 162 and 16b - how tough is this schedule? Would it be much harder if I added an “easier” tech like 188, 168, or 100?
history.subject: Should I add another tech to 162 and 16b?
